BASIC GIT COMMANDS
git --version           = to check the git version.
git init                = to initiate the git tracking thw working directory.
git add .               = to add all the changes to staging area.
git add (filename)        = to add a specific file to the staging area.
git commit -m "message" = to commit the changes to the local repo.
git status              = to check the git working directory status.
git log                 = to check the git commit logs.
git log --oneline       = to check the git commit logs in oneline.
git --ammend            = to change the message of the latest/last commit message.
git tag -a (tagname) commitid -m "message"  = to add tags to any commit by its commit id.
git tag -l              = to display the all the list of tags.
git show (tagname)      = to display changes in a particular tag name.

git clone (url)           = to clone the remote repo to a local repo.
git remote add (origin) (url) = to add origin remote repo.
git remote -v           = to list origin
git fetch               = to fetch any changes from the remote repo.

git push (origin) (master)
